Fall back to pread/pwrite when copy_file_range returns ENOSYS.

Some restricted runtime environments (gVisor, certain seccomp filters,
older kernels < 4.5) do not implement the copy_file_range(2) syscall and
return ENOSYS.  In that case the existing fallback (`break` to the
pread+pwrite loop below) should also kick in, but `.NOSYS` was being
swallowed by `else => unexpectedErrno(err)` instead, returning
`error.Unexpected` to the caller and causing zig itself to abort with
`thread N panic: TODO` while symbolising the resulting stack trace.

Mirroring the .INVAL / .XDEV branches with .NOSYS lets zig's own
caching code work transparently in those environments.

--- a/lib/std/posix.zig
+++ b/lib/std/posix.zig
@@ -6425,6 +6425,7 @@
                     .PERM => return error.PermissionDenied,
                     .TXTBSY => return error.SwapFile,
                     .XDEV => break, // support for cross-filesystem copy added in Linux 5.3, use fallback
+                    .NOSYS => break, // syscall unavailable (gVisor, old kernels, seccomp), use fallback
                     else => |err| return unexpectedErrno(err),
                 }
             }
